attributes.description: Agentcore runtime details dashboard showcasing runtime performance and operational health.

params.markdown:
# Agentcore runtime

This dashboard provides insights into the following:
- Agent runtime invocations and session metrics across endpoints
- Error monitoring, including system errors, user errors, and overall error trends
- Performance analysis with latency, duration, and throttling metrics
- Endpoint-specific analytics showing top performers by invocation and session counts

embeddableConfig.description: Shows the trend of invocations across all resources
embeddableConfig.title: Invocations

embeddableConfig.description: Shows the trend of agent sessions initiated.
embeddableConfig.title: Sessions

query.esql:
FROM logs-aws_bedrock_agentcore.runtime_application_logs-default |
KEEP @timestamp, aws.bedrock_agentcore.request_id, aws.bedrock_agentcore.resource_arn, gen_ai.prompt, trace.id, gen_ai.conversation_id
| SORT `@timestamp` desc
| RENAME aws.bedrock_agentcore.request_id as `Request ID`, gen_ai.conversation_id as `Session ID`, trace.id as `Trace ID`, aws.bedrock_agentcore.resource_arn as `Resource ARN`, gen_ai.prompt as `Prompt`, @timestamp as `Timestamp`
